Karen NIEDBALSKI, n/k/a Lukas, Respondent,
v.
Richard NIEDBALSKI, Appellant. No. ED 105163 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION THREE. Filed: December 26, 2017
Motion for Rehearing and/or Transfer to Supreme Court Denied February 26, 2018 FOR APPELLANT: Susan M. Hais, Dzenana Delic, 222 S. Central Ave., Ste. 600, Clayton, MO 63105. FOR RESPONDENT: Cynthia M. Howlett, 7711 Bonhomme Ave., Ste. 815, Clayton, MO 63105, Lawrence G. Gillespie, 120 South Central Ave., Ste. 650, Clayton, MO 63105. Before Gary M. Gaertner, Jr., P.J., Robert M. Clayton III, J., Angela T. Quigless, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

Richard Niedbalski appeals the judgment granting in part and denying in part his motion to quash garnishments filed by Karen Niedbalski, n/k/a Lukas. We find no error has occurred.

No jurisprudential purpose would be served by a written opinion. We have, however, provided the parties a memorandum setting forth the reasons for our decision.

The judgment of the trial court is affirmed under Rule 84.16(b).
